You should end up with the kettlebell straight above your head. Then let it swing back down so that you end up in a lowered squat position.
name: Single-Arm Kettlebell Snatch

instructions: Place a kettlebell between your feet. Squat down and grab it with one hand while keeping your back flat. Swing the kettlebell back between your legs and then quickly reverse the movement by thrusting your hips forward, swinging the kettlebell up until it reaches neck height. Let it fall back down in between your legs. Switch arm when you're done with all repetitions.
name: SIngle-Arm Kettlebell Swing

instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust the seat height so that the handles are at the same level as your lower chest. Pull your shoulders back and down, grab one of the handles and push. Keep abs tight throughout the movement to stabilisize your body, and begin very light as to let your body get used to the movement.
name: Single-Arm Machine Bench Press

instructions: Grab the handle with your hand facing inwards against you and hold onto the machine with your other hand for support. Pull down until you reach your upper chest with the handle and then slowly return it to its starting position.
name: Single-Arm Machine Chinup

instructions: Identical to regular pulldowns except that you will use one arm at a time. Grab the handle with the arm you intend on using and grab onto the machine with the other for stability. Pull the handle down towards your side and then slowly return it to its starting position. A great way to build up to those one arm pull-ups.
name: Single-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust the padding so that you can sit comfortably and reach the handles while your chest is pressed up against the pad. Reach for the handle with one arm and begin pulling it back as far as you can, squeeze your back muscles at the end of the movement for a second and then slowly let the handle all the way back. Finish your repetitions for one arm and then do them with the other arm.
name: Single-Arm Machine Row

instructions: Just like a regular Pull-Up except that you'll only use one hand a time. Hang freely and pull yourself all the way up until your chin is above the bar. Then lower yourself back down.
name: Single-Arm Pullup

instructions: Identical to a normal pushup, but you will be doing it with one hand at a time. Lie on the floor with one hand on the floor and the other one that you're not using behind your lower back. Then lower yourself down and push yourself back up. Do the repetitions for one arm and then the other.
name: Single-Arm Pushup

instructions: Stand on one leg at a time and squat down until your leg is parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Single-Leg Bodyweight Squat

instructions: Sit down in the machine with one resting on the floor and the other inside the machine. Curl the weight down as far as you can and squeeze your hamstrings as you do it, then let it back until your leg is fully extended. Switch leg after you've performed all repetitions with the other.
name: Single-Leg Curl in Machine

instructions: Sit in a leg press machine with both legs on the sled, placed a little wider than shoulder width apart and near the top of the sled. Press the sled all the way up and place one foot on the floor. Allow the sled weight to push the used leg down as far as comfortable and then push it back up until your leg is almost straight. That's a repetition. Switch leg after you've performed all repetitions for one leg.
name: Single-Leg Press

instructions: Sit in a leg press machine with both legs on the sled, placed a little wider than shoulder width apart and furthest down so that only the front part of your feet are in touch with it. Press the sled up with both legs and then lower one leg down so that you only have one foot on the sledge at a time, this will be your starting position. Let the weight push your foot all the way back (towards you) until you feel a great stretch in your calf muscle. Pause for a second and then press it all the way up so that your calf muscle is fully flexed. Switch leg after you're done with your repetitions for that leg. To maximize muscle contact, always pause at the bottom portion of the movement to avoid using your Achilles' heel.
name: Single-Leg Machine Calf Press

instructions: Do a regular sit-up.
name: Situp

instructions: Lie down on a flat bench in a smith machine. Unhitch the barbell when you're ready and begin the movement by lowering it down towards your chest. Then push it back up.
name: Smith Machine Bench Press

instructions: Have the barbell at the same height as your hips to start with. Grab it at a shoulder width grip and unhitch the barbell. Bend over forward until your torso is parallel to the floor. Pull the barbell towards your abs and then lower it back down. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Smith Machine Bent-Over Row

instructions: Stand up in a smith machine with a plate or some elevated object on the floor in front of you. Stand on it with the front of your foot and push yourself up through your foot. Then lower yourself back down. Tip: Stop for 1 second at the bottom of the movement.
name: Smith Machine Calf Raise

instructions: Lie down flat in a smith machine. Grab the barbell with a narrow grip. Begin the movement by lowering the barbell towards your chest and stop when it touches it. Then push it back up until your arms are straight.
name: Smith Machine Close-Grip Bench Press

instructions: Lie down on a declined bench in a smith machine. Unhitch the barbell when you're ready and begin the movement by lowering it down towards your lower chest. Then push it back up.
name: Smith Machine Decline Bench Press

instructions: Stand in a smith machine so that the barbell is resting on your hands and your elbows are pointing forward. Keep abs tight and squat down as far as you can, then stand back up.
name: Smith Machine Front Squat

instructions: Lie down on an inclined bench in a smith machine. Unhitch the barbell when you're ready and begin the movement by lowering it down towards your upper chest. Then push it back up.
name: Smith Machine Incline Bench Press

instructions: Arrange the smith machine so that you can get under the barbell while standing up straight. Put one leg in front and the other one behind you, your front legs knee should be right above your foot. Go down until your other knee touches the floor, and then stand back up. Switch leg after you've done your repetitions.
name: Smith Machine Lunge

instructions: Sit on a bench with the back support almost all the way up. Unhitch the weight at shoulder height and then press the weight up until your arms are fully stretched. Then lower it back down.
name: Smith Machine Overhead Press (Behind the Neck)

instructions: Stand up in a smith machine. Have the barbell hitched at the same height as your hips. Grab it at a shoulder wide grip and begin to lower it all the way down until your back is parallel to the floor or as far down as you can with a straight back. Keep abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Smith Machine Romanian Deadlift

instructions: Sit on a bench in a smith machine without the back support. Keep abs flexed to support your back throughout the movement and start off by unhitching the weight from the smith machine at shoulder level, then push it straight up and then lower it back down.
name: Smith Machine Shoulder Press

instructions: Sit on a bench with no back support. Unhitch the weight at shoulder height and then press the weight up until your arms are fully stretched. Then lower it back down.
name: Smith Machine Shoulder Press (Behind the Neck, Without Back Support)

instructions: Sit on a bench in a smith machine with the back support almost all the way up. Start the movement off by unhitching the weight from the smith machine at shoulder level, then push it straight up and then lower it back down.
name: Smith Machine Shoulder Press (with Back Support)

instructions: Stand in a smith machine and grab the barbell with a little wider than a shoulder width grip. Simply shrug the barbell up and then lower it back down until your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
name: Smith Machine Shrug

instructions: Stand in a smith machine and grab the barbell with a little wider than a shoulder width grip behind your back. Simply shrug the barbell up and then lower it back down until your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
name: Smith Machine Shrug (Behind the Back)

instructions: Stand in a smith machine and position yourself so that the barbell is resting on your upper back. Squat down until your legs are parallel to the floor and then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Smith Machine Squat

instructions: Begin in a prone position on the floor identical to as if you were about to do a pushup. Begin the movement by bringing one leg at a time as far forward as you can to your side, as if you were to touch the back of your shoulder with the knee. Return the leg to the starting position and switch leg.
name: Spider Crawl

instructions: Position yourself in front of a preacher bench so that you're looking at where you would usually sit. Grab the barbell from the seat and align your elbows with the padding of the bench and begin to curl. Use a shoulder wide grip.
name: Spider Curl

instructions: Get on your bike and follow the instructions given by the instructor.
name: Spinning

instructions: Get in the machine and set it up according to your preference. Hold onto the rails and press start to begin when ready. Tips: Try changing things up by taking smaller steps, or by doing longer steps and straightening your legs out more.
name: Stairmaster

instructions: Stand up in a shoulder wide stance and grab the barbell at a shoulder wide grip. Bend over forward and lower the barbell all the way down as far as you can or until your back is parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Stiff-Leg Deadlift (Wide Stance)

instructions: Stand in a pulldown machine and grab the bar at a shoulder wide width. Begin pushing downwards with your arms straight throughout the movement, stop when you're about to reach your thighs.
name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

instructions: Stand up and unrack the barbell so that it is resting just above your shoulders. Begin the movement by moving your head slightly back to allow the bar to travel in as a straight line up as possible. Push it up until your arms are fully straight, then lower it back down to shoulder height.
name: Strict Barbell Press

instructions: Position your feet under a barbell at a very wide stance. Squat down and grab the barbell so that your arms go down in between your legs. Grip should be shoulder wide or narrower. Simply stand up with the barbell. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Sumo Deadlift

instructions: Begin by standing with a wide stance as you would with a regular sumo deadlift. Grab the bar with a narrow grip that is inside of your legs. Arch your back and chest up, then begin the movement by deadlifting the weight up. As you stand up with the bar, continue the movement by shrugging the weight at the same time as you continuously pull it up towards your chin. Your arms should be straight until the end of the shrug. Then finish the movement off by lowering the barbell back to the floor.
name: Sumo Deadlift (High Pull)

instructions: Position your feet under a barbell at a very wide stance. Squat down and grab the barbell so that your arms go down in between your legs. Grip should be shoulder wide or narrower. Simply stand up with the barbell. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Sumo Deadlift (with Chain)

instructions: Get your swimming wear on and begin swimming.
name: Swimming

instructions: Grab a dumbbell in each hand and begin walking. If you're in a gym with limited space you can put a dumbbell on the floor a couple of meters ahead and walk towards it and back as many times as you want. The dumbbells should be heavy enough so that you can only walk back and forth a couple of times and barely be able to hold onto them once you're done.
name: Timed Farmer's Walk (with Dumbbells)

instructions: Grab a weight plate in each hand so that you're holding it with your fingers only. Begin to walk and hold onto the plate for as long as you can.
name: Timed Farmer's Walk (with Weight Plate)

instructions: Stand in a dip station and grab onto the bars while standing on the floor so that your elbows are pointing up towards the ceiling. Jump up into the starting position where your arms are straight, and lower yourself back down to the point where your elbows point towards the ceiling. If you feel shoulder or elbow discomfort it is recommended to stop when your arms are at a 90 degree angle. Push yourself back up until your arms are straight. Keep elbows tucked in as much as you can throughout the movement to target the triceps.
name: Triceps Dip

instructions: Rest your chest against the preacher pad. Start off the movement by simultaneously lowering the dumbbells all the way down until your arms are fully stretched. Then curl them back up.
name: Two-Arm Dumbbell Preacher Curl

instructions: Grab a barbell with an overhand grip at a little less than shoulder width apart. The barbell should be resting on your thighs with your arms almost straight, but not locked. Use the sides of your shoulders and lift the barbell up until it reaches neck height. Your elbows should move up and out to your sides. Then lower the bar back down to your thighs.
name: Upright Barbell Row

instructions: Stand in a cable machine and position the handle at a little above knee height. Your palms should be facing inwards against you. Grab it and pull all the way up to your chin and then lower it back down.
name: Upright Cable Row

instructions: Stand up and grab one dumbbell in each hand so that they're resting on the front of your thighs and your palms are facing inwards against you. Lift the dumbbells all the way up to your chin and then lower them back down.
name: Upright Dumbbell Row

instructions: Stand up and grab an Ez-Bar at the inner handles so that your palms are facing slightly inwards. Lift the barbell all the way up to your chin and then lower it back down.
name: Upright EZ-Bar Row

instructions: Place a V-bar handle on a pull-up-bar. Hang freely from it and pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Then lower yourself back down.
name: V-Bar Pullup

instructions: Prepare a clear way in the gym and set up two objects that mark the start and end of it. Begin the exercise by taking a big step forward with one leg at a time, lowering your body against the floor in each step until your rear knee almost touches the floor. Then raise your body back up and swap leg for your next step. The movement should be performed forward.
name: Walking Lunge

instructions: Setup your treadmill and begin walking.
name: Walking on Treadmill

instructions: Go for a walk.
name: Walking Outdoors

instructions: Grab a pair of weight plates of appropiate weight and hold them by your sides. Begin the movement by raising them straight up and forward while keeping your arms straight. Stop when they reach shoulder height and lower them back down until they are by your side again.
name: Weight Plate Front Raise

instructions: Stand up straight and grab a plate with both hands. With a very slight bend in the elbows, raise the plate until its slightly above shoulder height, and then lower it back down. Control the weight throughout the movement.
name: Weight Plate Front Raise

instructions: Grab a weight plate in each hand so that you're holding it with your fingers only. Raise it up so that it ends up in the middle of your palm and then let it roll out to your fingers again.
name: Weight Plate Squeeze

instructions: Just like regular Chins but you will either squeeze a dumbbell between your legs or wear a dip belt with a weight attached to it. Grab the pull-up bar at a shoulder width grip, with your palms facing you. Pull yourself up until your head is above your hands, squeeze your shoulder blades back and down as you come up and then slowly lower yourself back down until your arms are extended and you feel a stretch in your lats.
name: Weighted Chinup

instructions: Lie down flat on the floor with a weight plate or dumbbell behind your head. Hold onto it while keeping it behind your neck above the floor and lift your upper body towards the ceiling.
name: Weighted Crunch

instructions: Just like a regular Pull-Up but you will either hold a dumbbell between your legs, or wear a dip belt with weights attached to it. Grab the Pull-Up bar with a little wider than shoulder width grip, palms facing forward. Pull yourself up until your head is above your hands, squeeze for a moment and then slowly lower yourself back down until you can feel a stretch in your lats.
name: Weighted Pullup

instructions: Stand up and grab a barbell at a little wider than a shoulder width grip. Keep your elbows tucked in at your sides as you curl the barbell all the way up until it reaches shoulder level. Then lower it back down to your thighs.
name: Wide-Grip Barbell Curl

instructions: Sit down in a pulldown machine with the paddings adjusted so that they comfortably hold your legs down when you're holding the bar. Grab the wide pulldown bar with your palms facing forward at a little more than shoulder width apart. Slightly lean back so that you arch your lower back and puff your chest up, then pull the bar down by drawing your shoulders and upper arms down and back. Once the bar touches your chest, slowly begin to raise the bar back to the starting position, allowing your lat muscles to stretch out more the further up you go.
name: Wide-Grip Machine Lat Pulldown

instructions: Grab a barbell with an overhand grip at a little wider than shoulder width apart. The barbell should be resting on your thighs with your arms almost straight, but not locked. Use the sides of your shoulders and lift the barbell up until it reaches neck height. Your elbows should move up and out to your sides. Then lower the bar back down to your thighs.
name: Wide-Grip Upright Barbell Row

instructions: Have a barbell lay on a rack at same height as your hips. Put your arms under it so that the barbell rests at the bend of the arm. Stand up and then squat all the way down until your legs are parallel to the floor. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
name: Zercher Squat

instructions: Grab a dumbbell in each hand and rest your chest against a preacher pad. At the start of the movement your palms should be facing away from you and as you reach the end of the movement and your arms are fully stretched, turn the dumbbell around so that they are facing upwards and curl the weight back up. Repeat.
name: Zottman Curl
